Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the
heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave
to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook
in its own steam).

Halve, peel and slice the @Red Onion{1} as thinly as you can. Zest and cut the @Lime{1} into
wedges. Pop half the onion into a #small bowl{} and add half the lime juice and @Sugar{1%tsp}
for the pickle. Add a @salt{pinch}, mix together and set aside to pickle.

Cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} into thirds. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use
a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the Tenderstem® and remaining onion and season. Stir-fry, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add
a splash of @water{}, then cover with a #lid{} and allow to cook until tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.
Remove the veg from the pan and cover to keep warm.

While the broccoli cooks, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g} into a #medium bowl{}
with the @Cornflour{10%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Heat the (now empty) #frying pan{} on high heat with a generous drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot,
fry the chicken until slightly crispy, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn frequently to ensure it doesn't
burn.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the
> middle.

In the meantime, in a medium bowl, combine the @Gochujang Paste{50%g}, @Ketjap Manis{25%g},
@Honey{15%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Tomato Ketchup{1%tbsp} and @Water{125%ml} for the sauce.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Once the chicken is slightly crispy, lower the heat to medium, then add the garlic and
stir-fry, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the sauce into the pan until the chicken is coated. Bring to a boil, then lower the
heat and simmer until the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir the cooked veg through the sauce until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a squeeze of lime
juice from a lime wedge.

Taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and more lime juice if needed. Add a splash of
@water{} if the sauce is a little thick.

Fluff up your rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest. Share the zesty rice between
your #bowls{}.

Top with your gochujang chicken stir-fry and pickled onion.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%g} and serve with any remaining lime wedges
to finish. Enjoy.